      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T13:50:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a bit confusing to read - is the double underscore necessary?  Could it be a single underscore instead?\n\nIf the __ is required from elsewhere, please document it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "cb2605465b83ba2e71abd155bd5c06050a8af721",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0ae1a001_30a09b07",
        "filename": "perf/modules/alerts-page-sk/alerts-page-sk.js",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T14:26:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We use a single underscore for properties to denote protected.\nHere I am, outside of the element definition, storing extra data in a property\non the create-icon-sk, so I use the __ to avoid any collisions. d3js\nfollows the same convention storing things at __data__ on elements.",
      "parentUuid": "f91fa221_b53be43d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "cb2605465b83ba2e71abd155bd5c06050a8af721",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed40a085_21b86b73",
        "filename": "perf/modules/alerts-page-sk/alerts-page-sk.js",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T14:36:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree we want to avoid colliding with anything potentially on create-icon-sk.\n\nCould we instead use a namespace-like approach? i.e. skalerts_config? \n\nI\u0027m not super opposed to __ either, it just looks strange with .__ (I\u0027d like to avoid Morse code in my computer code)",
      "parentUuid": "0ae1a001_30a09b07",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "cb2605465b83ba2e71abd155bd5c06050a8af721",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4b1ce37c_c74d7663",
        "filename": "perf/modules/alerts-page-sk/alerts-page-sk.js",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T16:13:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I agree we want to avoid colliding with anything potentially on create-icon-sk.\n\u003e \n\u003e Could we instead use a namespace-like approach? i.e. skalerts_config? \n\nThen there\u0027s no indication that this isn\u0027t a native property of create-icon-sk.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e I\u0027m not super opposed to __ either, it just looks strange with .__ (I\u0027d like to avoid Morse code in my computer code)\n\nI would prefer to stick with __config, or I could go to __config__ to make it look closer to what d3js does.",
      "parentUuid": "ed40a085_21b86b73",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 59,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "cb2605465b83ba2e71abd155bd5c06050a8af721",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
